<item>
            <title>[HADOOP-10418] SaslRpcClient should not assume that remote principals are in the default_realm</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-10418</link>
                <project id="12310240" key="HADOOP">Hadoop Common</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In SaslRpcClient#getServerPrincipal, when constructing the KerberosPrincipal to compare to the configured value, we just assume that the remote principal is in the default realm configured in /etc/krb5.conf. This will not always be the case, however. Instead, we should use the configured domain_realm mapping to determine the realm of the remote principal.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12703006">HADOOP-10418</key>
            <summary>SaslRpcClient should not assume that remote principals are in the default_realm</summary>
